China May Invest Up to $5.64 Billion in Polish Power, Rzeczpospolita Says

-- B y   D a v i d   M c Q u a i d
-- 
2011-04-01T05:22:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-01/china-may-invest-up-to-5-64-billion-in-polish-power-rzeczpospolita-says.html
Chinese power and construction
companies have offered Polish partners up to 16 billion zloty
($5.64 billion) in financing and construction services to build
coal-fired power plants, the daily Rzeczpospolita reported,
citing Marek Frydrych, who represents the Chinese companies, and
Deputy Treasury Minister  Jan Bury .  Most advanced are talks between state-owned utility Energa
SA and Shanghai Electric Group Co. Ltd., which is ready to
finance 85 percent of the 5 billion-zloty to 6 billion-zloty
cost of building a new generating unit at Ostroleka, Frydrych
was quoted as saying on the newspaperâ€™s Rp.pl website.  China National Electric Equipment Corporation and Covec, or
the China Overseas Engineering Group Co., have expressed
interest in projects for new coal-fired plants by Enea SA in
Kozienice and Tauron Polska Energia SA in Jaworzno, Rp.pl
reported, without saying where it got the information.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
